frank lobdell figure drawings frank lobdell figure drawings an exhibition of approximately 60 figure drawings in ink pencil crayon and wash from the late 1950s to the mid 1960s frank lobdell participated in weekly evening figure drawing sessions with his friends richard diebenkorn elmer bischoff and david park essentially a nonfigurative artist lobdell used these weekly drawing sessions as a springboard to develop a vocabulary of abstraction that was informed by a study of the human body and grounded in the formal issues of expressionist gesture and line date and time ongoing every day from november 11 2009 through february 21 2010 11 00 am location cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map url http museum stanford edu audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members category exhibitions arts sponsor contact 723 4177 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed mondays and tuesdays and thanksgiving day december 23 24 25 download email event print use this permalink last modified october 30 2009
